</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,599,1870]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Derivation of specific epithet. Based on Latin 
<emphasis box="[854,901,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">ater</emphasis>
for black, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1149,1604,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biseta">
<emphasis box="[1079,1149,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">biseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the name of a similar species from which 
<taxonomicName box="[588,739,1644,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atribiseta">
<emphasis box="[588,739,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. atribiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the black frons.
</paragraph>
